  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Registry collecting data on use of The STAR™ Tumor Ablation System.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The STAR Prospective Registry is an observational registry to gather clinical safety and
      outcome data in patients with painful spinal metastases in the thoracolumbar spine (T1-L5)
      following targeted radiofrequency ablation (t-RFA) treatment with the STAR™ Tumor Ablation
      System.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
